The paper focuses on identifying and managing technical debts in software projects, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The proposed framework involves pattern recognition and machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses simulation studies, which could be related to software development (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
